# TypeScript StandardJS Rules

This project strictly follows the **StandardJS** philosophy: "Code is for humans to read; only incidentally for machines to execute."

- **No semicolons**: Do not end statements with `;`.
- **Single quotes**: Always use single quotes for strings (except when avoiding an escape).
- **Minimal configuration**: Avoid unnecessary boilerplate and verbose code — keep it concise and readable.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const message = "Hello World";
console.log(message);

// ✅ GOOD
const message = 'Hello World'
console.log(message)
```
